title: For Sale:  NIB H&K VP9 9mm
postcontent: Brand new in box HK VP9. Comes with hard case, 2 magazines, and multiple sized back and side straps. Please email with any questions. You can pick up in person or I can ship to your FFL. I accept cash, credit cards, and paypal. I will consider trades. If the ad is active then It is still available. Cash discount price $579. *please note* Texas residents must pay state sales tax.In development for more than four years, the VP9 is Heckler & Koch’s latest handgun and the first striker fired HK since the renowned P7 series pistols were introduced in the 1980s.      Experience gained by HK engineers with the recent P30 pistol had a direct influence on the design of the VP9, but the VP9 breaks new ground with its integration of a unique striker firing system with an enhanced HK “light pull” trigger. The net result is trigger quality unequaled in any production striker fired handgun. HK pioneered the first striker fired handguns, producing both the VP70 and P7 series, designs that impacted several models by HK competitors. But a superior trigger has eluded most striker fired pistol designs. The VP9 trigger surpasses those found on competitors. It has a short, light take-up with a solid, single action type break followed by a short positive reset. The VP9 trigger has a consistent pre-travel pull with a positive wall/crisp break. Typically, striker fired guns have a pre-travel pull that increases in weight as you go through the trigger stroke. With the VP9, you have a less than noticeable pre-travel pull until the trigger reaches the engagement point of the fire control parts prior to trigger break. The VP9 uses HK’s ergonomic handgun grip design that includes three changeable backstraps and six side panels— accommodating all hand sizes. Molded finger grooves in the front of the pistol’s grip also instinctively position an operator’s hand for optimal shooting. Only HK handguns have such a customized grip. Although influenced by other HK models, the VP9 has all the hallmarks of the latest, state-of-the-art handgun. All controls are completely ambidextrous. Slide releases are present on both sides of the frame and the magazine release can be easily activated by left- or right-handed shooters. A new feature is HK’s patented charging supports — simple components that are mounted on each side of the rear of the slide and provide better gripping leverage for racking the slide rearward. The charging supports speed reloading and make operating the VP9 easier for shooters with reduced hand strength. The VP pistols uses the proven P30 steel magazine; 15 and 10-round capacity available. The VP9 has an extended Picatinny MIL-STD-1913 rail molded into its polymer frame for mounting lights and accessories. The rail has been tested and certified to handle mounted accessories up to 5.6 ounces. The VP9’s proprietary captive flat recoil spring helps reduce the recoil forces effecting the operator and the handgun, improving shooter control during rapid firing and prolonging component service life. HK’s famous cold hammer forged barrel — made from cannon grade steel — ensures long service life. Similar HK barrels on 9 mm P30 models have fired more than 90,000 rounds in endurance tests in 2010. The polygonal bore profile, with no traditional lands-and-grooves rifling, contributes to longer service life as well as a slight increase in muzzle velocity. The VP9’s machined steel slide is protected from corrosion and wear by HK’s hostile environment finish and all metal components, including springs and pins have superior metallurgy. VP pistols are made in Heckler & Koch’s Oberndorf factory in southwest Germany. The VP9 is well-suited for civilian sport shooting, security, military, and law enforcement use. Covered by Heckler & Koch’s limited lifetime warranty, the HK VP9 is a solid design engineered with the famous long-term durability that make HK products especially cost-effective when subjected to total life cycle cost analysis.

Advanced Armament Corporation complete MPW rifles are chambered for 300 AAC BLACKOUT. (*All NFA rules apply)

A 30 caliber rifle the size of an AR15 5.56mm caliber rifle - without a reduction in magazine capacity. The AAC MPW in 300 AAC Blackout uses ordinary 223/5.56mm  magazines for a full 30 round capacity, and is available in 9, 12.5, and 16 inch barrels.*

Components are of premium quality. The 1:7 twist barrel is nitrided to provide extreme corrosion resistance and high hardness for a long life - outperforming chrome-lined barrels for longevity without the potential impediments to accuracy. The muzzle is threaded 5/8-24 and includes an AAC 51-tooth BLACKOUT™ flash suppressor with the complete upper. A Knight’s Armament free-floating URX III helps maintain accuracy while providing for the mounting of accessories. There is also a base layer of high-phosphorous electroless nickel that ensures the extreme corrosion protection that is absent from other Nickel Boron carriers that use a single, thinner layer. The bolt itself is Carpenter 158® phosphated shot-peened steel to ensure precise dimensions with no concerns for hydrogen embrittlement in the critical lug area. A special green o-ring that is tested to not bind even at -40 degrees F is standard. The extractor spring is made from premium ultra-strong wire and is a low fatigue design to ensure the longest possible life. The extractor pin made from 300 ksi S2 tool steel - not the much lower strength S7 more commonly used. 

Finally, a properly-staked carrier-key with Permatex® gasket-seal compound ensures no gas leakage. Optics, mounts, and silencer are not included.

title: For Sale:  Custom-Built, Brand NEW AR-15 (M4 style) Rifle - Plus Goodies - Plus 1,000 rounds .223/5.56 NATO
postcontent:
I had this rifle built with every customizable option I could opt for (more accurate barrel, nicer sights, tougher arm guards, extra magazines, a nice carry case, more positions inside the stock for setting length, etc etc etc). I got very excited over AR's last month with the flurry of AR sales all over the country, and couldn't resist using my tax returns(thanks Federals!) to get the nicest M4 I could find. Up until last week I had never even held an AR style rifle. But, once I got a chance to play with it, and inspect the internals, I realized that I just liked AK's much better. Call me old-school; I prefer my guns to be conscript-proofed. But now, my loss is your gain! (unless you're wanting to trade, which we'll get to in a minute)


     Price is firm, I'm actually taking a loss on the price(it was mostly the goodies, ammo, and new barrel that drove the price up), but I wound up not liking the AR as much as the AK, and with limited safe space, I'd rather sell this one off quick and take advantage of the AK sales going on right now.

    The manufacturer is nominally Bear Creek Arsenal, but that really only applies to the lower receiver, hand guard, and trigger assembly at this point. The rest were, as far as I'm aware, third-party options that Bear Creek offers in place of it's own standard parts. It was all through their customer service via the phone however; they do not offer those options online for whatever reason.


   Email me anytime with questions or if you'd like to buy her. This is a semi-automatic, .223/5.56 NATO chambered, M4 style rifle. Brand new, never fired(excepting the test rounds from the factory, which yes, are included. It strikes beautifully in case you're curious, and there are three test rounds), still in it's original packaging, original factory lube, manuals, everything. I opened it, dis-assembled it, figured out how it functioned, and put it back together and back in the case, deciding "meh, it's pretty, but damn, I should have bought another AK".


I apologize for the blurry gun photo; I have a very old phone with a low-quality camera. The other photo is stock.


Included, just to be perfectly clear:

-Bear Creek customized M4 style AR
-2 magazines, 30 rounds
-Hard carry case with foam inserts
-Manual/Safety pamphlets
-3 test rounds from factory with test date stamp
-1,000 rounds silver bear 5.56 NATO, all brand new, sealed in packaging.



Everything is new, never touched save for my one dis-assembly of the rifle, and opening one pack of 20 rounds to make sure they were all nice and pretty. Other than that it has sat in a humidity controlled safe, awaiting judgement.




TRADES:

   I'm looking primarily for cash, because frankly I just want to go get a very nice AK in this M4's place, but I will always consider trades. My current hunts are:



-Mosins of any type. Will trade direct if you have enough Mosins. Seriously; I love Mosins. Priority is given to non-91/30's, even though those are my favorite, I have plenty of the basic Mosins. That being said, ANY Mosin will get my attention.
-Mausers of any type(excepting the Spanish .308 models), I vastly, VASTLY prefer German WWI/WWII models, as opposed to Turkish, Yugoslavian, etc, but I will look at them all.
-AK's, somewhat obviously, the cheaper the better(I prefer to do my own upgrading)
-Maxim MG of any type, any style, any caliber
-Dragunov Sniper
-SVT-40(If you have this or the Maxim, you have my undivided attention. Both are one of the few pieces still missing from my Soviet Firearms collection)


   I think my ideal trade would be for an AK, plus a handful of Mosins. But that's a stretch that assumes Portland is full of people who collect Mosins, like myself. So offer away, the worst I can say is no. Shotguns are an automatic no, just to clarify. I have a 12ga, and that's really all the shotgun I ever need.

   I'm willing to consider partial trades and cash, or direct trades, or any combination we can think of. This is first come, first served, so email me ASAP if you'd like it; I can't imagine any AR sitting on Armslist for more than a few days, but then again I've never had one before, so what do I know!

    The only thing this M4 is missing, in my noobie opinion, is a proper scope, but that being said, the iron sights are already after-market upgraded, and they work beautifully.

title: For Sale:  Mosin-Nagant Model 1891/30
postcontent:
Mosin-Nagant Model 1891/30. Manufactured by the Izhevsk arsenal in 1935, this rifle was later re-arsenaled as stock and receiver markings attest. I bought it in February 2003, and it was unissued since the re-arsenal. Even today it still has varnish on the sling estutcheons. I have fired fewer than 40 rounds through it and kept it meticulously clean and protected, with its condition reflecting this care.  See photos.  It has matching serial numbers on the receiver, bolt, buttplate, bayonet, and magazine floorplate (floorplate has been renumbered during the arsenal rebuild and the old number is lightly visible and lined through). The bore is clean and bright and has not been counterbored. Trigger has a crisp break. There is a discreet import mark on the underside of barrel for TG KNOX TN. This rifle comes with the following original arsenal-provided accessories: cleaning rod, bayonet, dog collar sling, and oil bottle.

A US Ordnance Corps manual for this rifle may be viewed online at stevespages.com/pdf/mosin-nagant.pdf.

Face to face transaction preferred.  Buyer must present government picture ID showing you are a resident of Ohio of legal age to purchase this firearm.
